# When asked to code a task
When you are asked to code a task from [implementation-tasks.mdc](mdc:.cursor/specifications/implementation-tasks.mdc):
1. Review the @main-project-specifications.mdc
2. Identify the task in [implementation-tasks.mdc](mdc:.cursor/specifications/implementation-tasks.mdc)
3. Start the task
4. Compile with `mvn clean verify`
5. Run unit tests with `mvn test`
6. Mark the task with an "x", example:`- [x] example task`
7. Commit changes
8. The task is now complete and you can ask to move on to the next task.